                  <p>Each test consists of a series of 10 items* - 2 at each of the levels below:</p>
                  <table class="table-level">
                    <tr>
                      <td id="level-ilr1">ILR 1</td>
                      <td>Elementary</td>
                      <td id="level-ilr2">ILR 2</td>
                      <td>Limited Working</td>
                      <td id="level-ilr3">ILR 3</td>
                      <td>General Professional</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td id="level-ilr1p">ILR 1+</td>
                      <td>Elementary Plus</td>
                      <td id="level-ilr2p">ILR 2+</td>
                      <td>Limited Working Plus</td>
                      <td id="level-ilr3p"></td>
                      <td id="level-ilr3pb"></td>
                    </tr>
                  </table>
                  <p>*An item consists of</p>
                  <ul>
                    <li>one prompt – A prompt consists of a video, audio and/or text file designed to elicit a spoken response from the candidate, and
                    </li>
                    <li>A benchmark response (BMR). The BMR is a candidate response which has been validated outside the system as being 'at level'.The BMR associated with a ‘Level 1 – Banking’ prompt is a response from someone speaking at ILR level 1, with the typical
                      strengths and weaknesses of a level 1 speaker.</li>
                  </ul>
                  <p>Here's an example of an item:</p>
                  <table class="table-pnp">
                    <tr>
                      <th>Audio</th>
                      <th>Benchmark (BMR)</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td><p>“What questions would you ask to gather the information below? For example, to gather someone's age, you might say 'How old are you?' What would you say if you wanted to find out about a person's:</p>
