                  <p>The candidate sees/hears each prompt in order, beginning with the Elementary level, and then must record their spoken responses. They can repeat each prompt once.
Then they click on ‘Record my Response.’</p>
                </div>
                <div class="tab-pane" id="3a">
                  <p>All tests will be split apart and rated prompt by prompt, starting with the highest level responses (General Professional) and descending until a Final Rating is assigned. Raters can click on ‘play’ buttons to</p>
                  <ul>
                    <li>See/hear the prompt,</li>
                    <li>Hear the Candidate Response (CR), and the</li>
                    <li>Hear the Benchmark Response (BMR)*.
                    </li>
                  </ul>

                  <p>Once they have listened to the Candidate Response in full, they are asked to decide whether the Candidate Response was</p>
                  <ul>
                    <li>better than,</li>
                    <li>as good as, or</li>
                    <li>worse than</li>
                  </ul>
                  <p>the BMR.</p>

